The old inscriptions vary, but in such a manner as to show that none of them have any weight or authority. Torrentius mentions three MSS. which are headed “Ad Virgilium Unguentarium urbis discriptio (the common blunder for ‘de- scriptio') Pamenetice,” and he himself adopts this absurdity, derived from v. 17.
